---
import { Carousel } from "webcoreui/astro";
import "../../styles/projects.css";
---

<div id="firefly" class="project-card">
    <div class="space-y-4 md:landscape:w-1/2">
        <h3 class="font-bold">Firefly</h3>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-400">
            An Terminal User Interface (TUI) based audio player
        </h4>
        <ul class="font-bold text-blue-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>First Commit: 2025-07-14</li>
            <li>Most Recent Commit: 2025-07-17</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Written in Rust, featuring <a
                class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
                href="https://crates.io/crates/rodio"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">Rodio</a
            > (an audio playback library) and <a
                class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
                href="https://ratatui.rs/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">Ratatui</a
            > (a TUI framework). It runs on terminals, using minimal memory, which
            can be useful alongside a resource-intensive application. <br /><br
            />It only supports FLAC, MP3, Vorbis, and WAV as of now. I plan to
            utilize <a
                class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
                href="https://ffmpeg.org/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">ffmpeg</a
            > to enable more formats.<br /><br />
            Though the design and functionality are currently limited, I plan to
            keep adding more features and polish the interface.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a
                class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
                href="https://github.com/cyandizy/firefly"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Repository</a
            >
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="md:landscape:w-1/2">
        <Carousel items={3}>
